title: The Grateful Dead Live at Edmundson Pavilion, U of Washington on 1974-05-21
description:
Set 1

Me & My Uncle, Brown Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, Deal, Mexicali Blues, It Must Have Been The Roses, The Race is On, Scarlet Begonias, El Paso, Row Jimmy, Money Money, Ship of Fools, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow-> China Doll

Set 2

Playin' In The Band, U.S. Blues, Big River, Stella Blue, Around & Around, Eyes Of The World-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
Really Good Show Another Wall of Sound delight. Quite a bit of hiss and a little distortion and interference due to recording and generations but the sound is still there and it's a well-played show by a very competent band. Thanks to the purveyors of this concert. I'll betcha it took a ton of work to preserve.

Lots of good solid versions of songs. First set highlight for me was the song off the Mars Hotel album "Money Money." This song was blasted by the women's groups and summarily dropped by the band from the repertoire, but I liked it, and this a hot version of it. The entire second set is primo.

The playing deserves a 5 star and the presentation is a 3. All in all a lot of fun.
